\pard\plain \fi720\sl288\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 A witch stood atop the tallest plateau in the Goree mountains. She stood alone, hiding, as was her custom, from the .}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 To the east, she saw red hills sloping gently into brittle valleys. Those rivers were dry, drained by industries of war. To the west, the mountains coursed down into a brown plain. That plain held its own rare clime, with niches for lichens that crawled along ground, sipping mist, for broad leafed plants with crenelated flowers that only opened with the moon. Brilliant red jawflies flitted from leaf to leaf, surviving on nothing but seeds. But, in the eyes of those who stood on that plain, it was nothing but flat ground; a choice sight for a battlefield. Every Spark in all the world had picked a side.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The northern army was her own. She had worked these last hundered years to fight for her purpose. They had chosen it. }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Each lightning gleam was followed by a burst of trumpeting, as though the followers of the storm god had come together undaunted by the force of the\~tempest to hold a play in honour of their great deity. It is impossible to give any idea of the impressiveness of this act of worship. From out the impenetrable darkness, between long lines of rain, like a sword from its scabbard leapt the dazzling flash. The branches of the sacred grove moaned and swayed, bitumen dark against this more than daylight brilliance; while, from beneath their shade, each burst of flame was answered by a blare of savage trumpets, the sound subsumed by the drum of the sequent thunder.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 So long as the storm lasted the strange music continued, broken now and again by the cries of the terrified cattle, which rose in chorus from countless byres and were hardly distinguishable at times from the rude horns blown by their owners.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Their enemy was innumerable. Men. Women. Demons. These miscreants poured forth from frothing holes near the distant sea. They sustained their long march to reach this chosen site by consuming each other. They chewed as they walked, with bits and pieces falling from their mouths, such that that their long battle line left a trail of picked clean bones behind them. Those who had eaten much had grown near to the size of god-eaters, tall as small mountains themselves, mounds of flesh, roped along on rolling logs, birthing more demons to swell their ranks.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Are you worried that He will hear us? He can\u8217\'92t. He is too far away.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Grumble.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Oh, please. I know that you do not fear Him the way you did when you were a child. We\u8217\'92ve both been alive too long. For us, a bright god is little more than a reading light.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 A scowl.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I\u8217\'92m exaggerating. I only mean to highlight how, after these many years, I\u8217\'92ve begun to lose the sense that a god\u8217\'92s essence is greater. Hide behind that scowl, if you must. I know your feelings. They are the same as mine. We\u8217\'92ve both been stewing in the futility of divine plans for }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1\cf1 quite}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1  a while. Look at our armies. Compared to the quaking earth we mustered when we were young, this is pitiable. We\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92ve been slacking. But then, why should we  care about the battle to end all battles when it has all happened one hundred and twenty times before? One side will be victorious, and how does it go from there? The remnants of the defeated will find some foothold to nurse their strength, and the fight will start all over again.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Signaling that fight is about to begin.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I\u8217\'92m almost embarrassed that it took me so long to realize that this conflict will never end. Not so long as He is watching. You know it, too.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Yes, I know it.\u8221\'94 First words to this woman in one hundred thousand years was to doubt her god.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Pel sensitive to it. World changign to hear the voice of woman.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I had a dream.\u8221\'94 \u8220\'93I discovered a word which could contain them. I assembled a chorus to chant Their names. If you had heard the names repeated,\u8221\'94 she said fervently, \u8220\'93each note entering on the finger, each new voice swelling the chord until the wash of noise did shake the earth\u8230\'85such was the echo that one and twenty voices blossomed into twelve and thousands!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 She was speaking now to the sky, to the stars beyond the rock, and Elrahet thought he saw a younger face beneath her wrinkling years. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93It did subdue Him,\u8221\'94 she claimed. \u8220\'93For an age of peace, it stilled His being.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 A quirked brow.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93But it was not enough. They broke free. Then I woke back up into this nightmare. Then and there I resolved to be done with all of this.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Motioning broadly.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You are giving up?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93No. I intend to end it. I\u8217\'92ve been delving into the mysteries of the Black.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1\cf1 what}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 !?"}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93So you\u8217\'92ve thought of it, too?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 I dont want to just outlive him. i want to visit him on his death bed and remind him that we all turn to dust, and that despite all his ambitions he will never be old enough to see them. Despite how genius of a guy he thinks he is, all that's left for him is an eternity of nothingness at best, and an eternity of hell at worst. I want him to know that his entire life project was nothing but a waste of his life, and the only thing he will experience for the short time he has left is me staring at him }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 When the deed is done, all conventions will be ruin. The next time we meet, it will be death.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 She hadn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t assentd but the enemy had read her }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Elrahet flies up into space. To watch it happen.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Solraheen, the god of her creation, sitting there on the barren ground like a fallen star.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 She pops up into space. Gets the black.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 scrap of shadow\line }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Tempted orbit.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Scar contracture }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Eccliptic plane}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Material boiled away, denuded of volatile material,}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Thoughts turned through central bank operations, the lonely first era, the currency denomination of trade in the early modern period, the causes of the fall of civilization, Bretton Woods, the fiscal profligacy of LBJ\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s Great Society programs, the creation of the eurodollar, the internal mental states of 70\u8217\'92s Keynesian economists, the origins of money, the operation of foreign exchange markets, the Volcker shock, Newtonian mechanics and gravity wells, derivatives and the rise of modern hedge funds, the causes of the Bolshevik revolution, the origins and motivations of the Federal Reserve, and TARP. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Into more primitive categories of thought}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 A separate accident, their existence, arbitrary. Inverted by a caprice of power. The true tragedy of tragic choices is that they\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92re unchosen.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Compet impact}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The battle explodes. Lines of fate tying. The demosn fall upon eachother. The gods lost the root of their power. A hunt which lasted for an age.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
